Bland sushi, rude to customers.  Several orders, both online and on phone, I requested no disposables which they ignored, sending plastic utensils and chopsticks that I don't need (I'm at home, why would I need them? Plus, it's needlessly wasteful).  When I called to complain, the person on the phone said "they don't look at the special instructions" on the online orders (they apparently don't for phone orders, either).  I also complained that my calamari order, at $7.95, had a stingy 8 pieces in it, which comes to a dollar a piece (see below).  She talked to the chef and he said he always adds 9, which is still stingy, but in this case, wrong.  When I tried to reiterate that mine had less than that she interrupted me, several times, and would not listen to what I had to say.  I've worked in restaurants and this kind of adversarial attitude towards customers is unacceptable. I would have been fired for talking to a guest like this.  When she continued to talk over me, I lost my temper, yelled at her, and hung up, which is not cool, I admit:  ordering from here put me in a bad mood.  There are not many great food options in this neighborhood, but it would be better to patronize somewhere else.  Judging from other reviews, if they make a mistake with your order, they'll blame you. I won't be ordering from here again.
